https://grpc-testing.appspot.com/job/gRPC_pull_requests/9070/

which says there are 3 failures, but lists only two:
1) tests.vsprojects/Debug/concurrent_connectivity_test.exe
2) tests.bins/asan/set_initial_connect_string_test polling=legacy

Looking at other Jenkins builds these seem flaky:
(1) fails here:
https://grpc-testing.appspot.com/job/gRPC_pull_requests/9072/

(2) fails here:
https://grpc-testing.appspot.com/job/gRPC_pull_requests/9075/

@rjshade it looks like @ctiller  has restarted the tests for you and thing seems to be fine (except the known flakes that you've mentioned).  What we've seen before was probably an intermittent problem on Jenkins, but I wanted to double check first. 

Sorry for the delay, I was only trying to protect stability of our unit tests and sometimes that slows people down (but pays off in the long run).
@jtattermusch thanks, and no need to apologize for the delay, totally reasonable to make sure the test failures are explained before merging.
